Of course. The documents of zimg is written in Chinese so you don&#x27;t know how to use.<p>1. Using curl and multiform way can post file to zimg and will return a html result:<p>curl -F &quot;blob=@testup.jpeg;type=image/jpeg&quot; &quot;<a href="http://127.0.0.1:4869/upload&quot;" rel="nofollow">http://127.0.0.1:4869/upload&quot;</a><p>If you don&#x27;t like upload files via multiform way, you can use raw post way. Use this command to upload image via raw post:<p>curl -H &quot;Content-Type:jpeg&quot; --data-binary @testup.jpeg &quot;<a href="http://127.0.0.1:4869/upload&quot;" rel="nofollow">http://127.0.0.1:4869/upload&quot;</a><p>You need tell zimg a header &quot;Content-Type&quot;, the value is the type of image.
This way will get a json result and the error message is in the table below:<p>{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:0,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;Internal error.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:1,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;File type not support.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:2,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;Request method error.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:3,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;Access error.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:4,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;Request body parse error.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:5,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;Content-Length error.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:6,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;Content-Type error.&quot;}}
{&quot;ret&quot;:false,&quot;error&quot;:{&quot;code&quot;:7,&quot;message&quot;:&quot;File too large.&quot;}}<p>2. Upload and download access control. Just modify conf file like this:<p>upload_rule   = &#x27;allow 127.0.0.1;allow xx.xx.xxx.xxx/xx&#x27;
download_rule = &#x27;allow all&#x27;<p>The conf rule is like nginx.<p>3. Sorry for missing English documents.
